# Language

## English (default)

Use English for:

- Source code identifiers (variables, functions, types, files, folders)
- Comments and JSDoc
- Commit messages, PR titles/bodies, and branch names (except the `V-<n>` prefix)
- Linear implementation comments from the agent (unless asked otherwise)
- Test descriptions (`it("returns unauthorized when session is missing")`)
- Logs and internal error codes

## Portuguese (pt-BR) — user-facing only

Use pt-BR **only** for text shown to end users:

- UI labels, buttons, placeholders, empty states
- Toast / alert messages
- Auth emails and user notifications (when we own the copy)
- `metadata` title/description when user-visible

## Examples

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
const itemName = formData.get("name");
throw new Error("Missing Supabase session"); // internal
return { error: "Não foi possível salvar o item." }; // user-facing

// ❌ BAD
const nomeItem = formData.get("name");
throw new Error("Sessão do Supabase ausente"); // internal in pt-BR
```

Do not mix languages in the same identifier or file naming scheme.
